</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>For any type <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> we have a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link> <fr:tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, {A}</fr:tex> equipped with a unit map <fr:tex>\eta _{ \mathsf {prop}} \colon  A  \to \mathsf {toProp} \, {A}</fr:tex>; moreover, we have the following induction principle: for any family of <fr:link
href="erct-001H.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001H">propositions</fr:link> <fr:tex>B \colon   \mathsf {toProp} \, A  \to   \mathsf {Prop}</fr:tex>, any function <fr:tex>b \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }  B \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{ \mathsf {prop}} \, x \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex> extends to a function <fr:tex>b^ \sharp   \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }  Bx</fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>When we have an element of <fr:tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, A</fr:tex>, we will say that <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is <fr:em><fr:strong>inhabited</fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
